  README for Trafodion Command Interface (TrafCI) Installation
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------

  Distributed files
  -----------------
  README                - This README file
  trafciInstaller.jar   - For Windows & any *nix platforms


  INSTALL:
  --------
  On *nix platforms (all unix variants including linux), the only supported
  installation method is using the command line install (trafciInstaller.jar).

  For more details, please refer to the Trafodion Command Interface Guide.

  For Windows platforms, TrafCI supports two different installation methods.

  Method 1: Use the trafciInstaller.jar file for command line install. 
            This is similar to the installation method for *nix platforms. 

            a.) Set JAVA_HOME/bin to your PATH
	    b.) To install, java -jar trafciInstaller.jar cm
                Set the location for Type4 jar file and set the location to install trafci

  Method 2: GUI Installer. On Windows machine double click on trafciInstaller.jar file and following the instructions on the dialog.


Output of a command line install:
---------------------------------
******************************************************************
***                                                            ***
*** Welcome to Trafodion Command Interface Installer           ***
***                                                            ***
***                                                            ***
***    NOTE: The installer requires the JDBC Type 4            ***
***          Driver to be installed on your workstation.       ***
***                                                            ***
******************************************************************

Type Y for a standard installation, or N for optional components only.

Standard Installation [Y]: Y

JDBC Type 4 Driver JAR File
-----------------------------
Enter the location and file name [/usr/local/trafci/jdbcT4.jar]: 


Trafodion Command Interface
--------------------------------
Enter the installation directory [/usr/local/]:.
Extracted 18 files from the
/tmp/trafciInstaller.jar
archive into the
/tmp/clients/trafci
directory.

Core TRAFCI files installed.
